Nigeria’s Asset Management Company Seeks Bonds Limit of 4.5 Trillion Naira

-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 
2011-08-30T12:47:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/nigeria-s-asset-management-company-seeks-bonds-limit-of-4-5-trillion-naira.html
Asset Management Corp. of  Nigeria 
plans to raise the limit of its bonds issuance program to 4.5
trillion naira, from 3 trillion naira, the Abuja-based company
that was set up by the government to buy banks’ bad debts, said
in a notice published in ThisDay newspaper.  An “extra ordinary general meeting of bondholders” of the
company, also known as Amcon, will be held on Sept. 30 in Lagos,
Nigeria’s commercial capital, to consider and approve the plan,
according to the notice.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dulue Mbachu at 
 dmbachu@bloomberg.net  